# Tools Reference

This file should match the callable tool surface declared in `server/gemini-tools.ts`.

## Core agent loop

| Tool | What it does |
|---|---|
| `terminal` | Execute a shell command and return stdout/stderr. Use this for installed CLIs and local shell workflows. |
| `get` | Read a file or URL. Supports `editor:` and `client:` prefixes. |
| `put` | Write content to a file. Supports `editor:` and `client:` prefixes. |
| `write` | Write markdown content into the chat window without ending the turn. |
| `end_turn` | End the current tool-response loop and return control to the user. |
| `append` | Append content to a named log file. |
| `say` | Generate HD voice output asynchronously. |
| `soundboard` | Play a browser-side synthesized sound effect such as `ding`, `success`, `rimshot`, `airhorn`, or `womp_womp`. |

## Google Workspace and communications

### Gmail

| Tool | What it does |
|---|---|
| `gmail_list` | List recent inbox messages. |
| `gmail_read` | Read a message by ID. |
| `gmail_search` | Search Gmail using Gmail query syntax. |
| `gmail_send` | Send an email. |

### Drive

| Tool | What it does |
|---|---|
| `drive_list` | List Google Drive files. |
| `drive_read` | Read a Drive file by ID. |
| `drive_search` | Search Google Drive files. |
| `drive_create` | Create a new Drive file. |
| `drive_update` | Update a Drive file. |
