## Search, web, and API access

| Tool | What it does |
|---|---|
| `web_search` | Search the web using Google or Exa-backed search. |
| `exa_search` | Search the web using Exa directly. |
| `http_get` | Make an authenticated or unauthenticated HTTP GET request. |
| `http_post` | Make an HTTP POST request. |
| `http_put` | Make an HTTP PUT request. |
| `http_patch` | Make an HTTP PATCH request. |
| `http_delete` | Make an HTTP DELETE request. |

## Browser and computer control

### Puppeteer browser automation

| Tool | What it does |
|---|---|
| `puppeteer_navigate` | Navigate the browser to a URL. |
| `puppeteer_click` | Click an element by selector. |
| `puppeteer_type` | Type text into an element by selector. |
| `puppeteer_screenshot` | Capture a browser screenshot. |
| `puppeteer_evaluate` | Execute JavaScript in the page context. |
| `puppeteer_content` | Return current page content as HTML or text. |

### Desktop computer-use tools

| Tool | What it does |
|---|---|
| `computer_screenshot` | Capture the current desktop state. |
| `computer_click` | Click screen coordinates. |
| `computer_move` | Move the mouse without clicking. |
| `computer_type` | Type text into the focused desktop target. |
| `computer_key` | Press a key, optionally with modifiers. |
| `computer_scroll` | Scroll the active window. |
| `computer_wait` | Wait before taking the next action. |

## Data and persistence

### Database tools

| Tool | What it does |
|---|---|
| `db_tables` | List database tables and schemas. |
| `db_query` | Run a read-only `SELECT` query. |
| `db_insert` | Insert a row into a table. |
| `db_delete` | Delete rows from a table with a required `WHERE` condition. |

### To-do tools

| Tool | What it does |
|---|---|
| `todo_list` | List active to-do items. |
| `todo_add` | Add a to-do item. |
| `todo_update` | Update a to-do item. |
| `todo_complete` | Mark a to-do item complete. |
| `todo_remove` | Remove a to-do item permanently. |

## Environment and device control

| Tool | What it does |
|---|---|
| `cast` | Control Chromecast and Google Nest devices through the `catt` CLI. |
| `camera` | Control the PTZ IP camera. |
| `set_mood_light` | Set the HP mood light state. This is currently a stub. |

## Guidance

1. When you need shell access, say explicitly that you are using the **`terminal` tool**.
2. When you need spoken output, use **`say`**.
3. When you need short feedback, comic timing, alerts, or cues, use **`soundboard`**.
4. Use **`end_turn`** to finish the turn. No other tool ends the loop.
